<paragraph blockId="42.[136,1452,1713,2084]" box="[189,937,1782,1807]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Etymology. The specific name is derived from the 
<typeStatus box="[730,776,1783,1807]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
locality; noun.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[136,1452,1713,2084]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Diagnosis. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lin, Pham &amp; Li, 2009" authorityName="Lin, Pham &amp; Li" authorityYear="2009" box="[621,1009,1817,1841]" class="Arachnida" family="Ochyroceratidae" genus="Speocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulbiformis">
<emphasis box="[621,770,1817,1841]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. bulbiformis</emphasis>
Lin, Pham &amp; Li, 2009
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the very long afferent spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[385,483,1852,1876]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="46.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@46.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figure 35. Speocera melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366995/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 35B</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lin, Pham &amp; Li" authorityYear="2009" box="[502,651,1852,1876]" class="Arachnida" family="Ochyroceratidae" genus="Speocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulbiformis">
<emphasis box="[502,651,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">S. bulbiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short afferent spermathecae (Lin 
<emphasis box="[1054,1107,1852,1876]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
, 2009: figs 4B, E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[136,1452,1713,2084]" lastBlockId="43.[136,1451,236,399]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Description. Female. Total length 1.21; carapace length 0.54; carapace width 0.44; abdomen length 0.60; abdomen width 0.48. Prosoma: carapace pyriform, narrowing gradually anteriorly; shiny, light yellow, suffused with purplish pattern (
<figureCitation box="[144,242,1956,1980]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="46.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@46.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figure 35. Speocera melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366995/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 35C</figureCitation>
); pars cephalica flat; fovea not visible. Sternum light yellow, suffused with purplish color, longer than wide (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="46.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@46.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figure 35. Speocera melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366995/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 35D</figureCitation>
). Endites light yellow, suffused with purplish tinge; with serrula; labium light yellow, suffused with purplish tinge. Clypeus nearly vertical; short. Chelicerae light yellow; promargin with a series of six teeth reaching the lamina; retromargin with two very small denticles (
<figureCitation box="[483,576,2059,2084]" captionStart="Figure 58" captionStartId="73.[154,217,2026,2048]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,233,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-98@73.[188,1398,233,2011]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="Figure 58. Female chelicerae of Speocera spp., anterior view. A. S. balikpapan Li &amp; Li sp. nov. B. S. batang Li &amp; Li sp. nov. C. S. bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov. D. S. cuyapo Li &amp; Li sp. nov. E. S. dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov. F. S. griswoldi Li &amp; Li sp. nov. G. S. huifengi Li &amp; Li sp. nov. H. S. huisun Li &amp; Li sp. nov. I. S. melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov. J. S. tabuk Li &amp; Li sp. nov. Scale bars=0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367045/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 58I</figureCitation>
). Eyes: six contiguous eyes surrounded by black pigmentation; 
<collectionCode box="[1288,1343,2060,2083]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">PME</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1399,1451,2060,2084]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">ALE</collectionCode>
subequal, 
<collectionCode box="[245,292,237,260]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">PLE</collectionCode>
largest (
<figureCitation box="[385,483,236,260]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="46.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@46.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figure 35. Speocera melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366995/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 35C</figureCitation>
). Opisthosoma oval; purplish (
<figureCitation box="[814,913,236,260]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="46.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@46.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figure 35. Speocera melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366995/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 35D</figureCitation>
). Legs light yellow; leg lengths I 1.98 (0.56, 0.16, 0.59, 0.38, 0.29); 
<collectionCode box="[321,339,271,294]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">II</collectionCode>
1.79 (0.52, 0.16, 0.50, 0.35, 0.27); 
<collectionCode box="[706,735,271,294]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">III</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[744,772,271,294]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">IV</collectionCode>
missing. Genitalia. Internal genitalia with afferent spermathecae long, extending past the sides of the abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[638,736,305,330]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="46.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@46.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figure 35. Speocera melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366995/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 35B</figureCitation>
); spermathecae long, oval (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1128,305,330]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="46.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-62@46.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Figure 35. Speocera melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366995/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 35A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[136,1451,236,399]" box="[189,370,340,364]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[136,1451,236,399]" box="[189,707,375,399]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Distribution. Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[568,614,375,399]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
